[{"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T20:39:51+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration of Google\u2019s wordmark, written in red and pink on a dark blue background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/f1vVd9z42phB1rL9Y-OHgVBPsG4=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73478177/STK093_Google_06.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"l09AdD\">Google made nearly $85 million over the past few months as revenue from its Search and cloud computing businesses soared. That\u2019s according to the quarter two earnings report released by <a href=\"https://abc.xyz/assets/19/e4/3dc1d4d6439c81206370167db1bd/2024q2-alphabet-earnings-release.pdf\">Google's parent company, Alphabet</a>, on Tuesday, which says Search alone raked in $48.5 million.</p>\n<p id=\"Jh37SK\">Meanwhile, Google\u2019s cloud division hit $10 million for the first time while also achieving $1 billion in operating profit. During an earnings call on Tuesday, Google CEO Sundar Pichai said the company\u2019s generative AI solu", "id": 916621, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204618/google-search-ai-q2-2024-earnings-results", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Google had a massive quarter thanks to Search and AI", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T20:21:27+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Tesla\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/BF1IGO5rPYCCjf_PRf4G-9LNOHo=/0x0:6000x4000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73478121/2157567959.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Osmancan Gurdogan / Anadolu via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"MDJToO\">Tesla published its <a href=\"https://ir.tesla.com/#quarterly-disclosure\">second quarter earnings report</a>, in which the company said it earned $1.48 billion in net income on $25.5 billion in revenue. That represents a 2 percent increase year over year compared to $24.9 billion in revenue in Q2 2023 but a 45 percent drop in net income.</p>\n<p id=\"hfjdls\">Tesla\u2019s gross margins were in the spotlight again, as bullish investors hoped to see improvements after years of steady decline. Rampant price cutting and cooling demand as well as cheaper financing have pushed the company\u2019s once-vaunted margins to their lowest point in six years. </p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><a", "id": 916622, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24201234/tesla-q2-2024-earnings-robotaxi-ai-cybertruck", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Tesla\u2019s profits sank sharply in the second quarter of 2024", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T19:48:29+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The location of the ESR Geo Wallet being pinpointed by the iPhone\u2019s Find My app.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ChQLjEPdijcuF-AtDSZCpD7HQE0=/1x0:982x654/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73477837/esr_geo_wallet.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>You won\u2019t need to stuff an AirTag inside ESR\u2019s Geo Wallet to find it.</em> | Image: ESR</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"EVspuC\">With its own integrated tracking module compatible with Apple\u2019s Find My network and a traditional bifold design, ESR\u2019s Geo Wallet can be located using an iPhone if it goes missing and without the bulge of an AirTag stuffed inside.</p>\n<p id=\"p8JLlq\">There\u2019s no shortage of wallets designed to accommodate an AirTag or <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22996801/chipolo-card-spot-review-find-my\">credit card-sized trackers such as the Chipolo</a>, but by using its own tracking module with a rechargeable lithium battery that\u2019s only 1.6 millimeters thick, the bifold Geo W", "id": 916623, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204465/esr-wallet-apple-find-my-tracking-airtag", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Stuff this trackable wallet with everything but an AirTag", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T19:31:38+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Kakao Office and Store as Founder Faces Arrest in Market Manipulation Case\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ZmhpsHNYjSlmkfEylpngRceptiI=/0x2:5000x3335/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73477808/2162462726.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Every Korean, Korean American, or K-pop fan you know probably has the KakaoTalk app.</em> | Photo: Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"VerX1w\">Kakao Corp. founder Kim Beom-su <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/07/22/business/kakao-founder-arrest-warrant-south-korea.html#:~:text=Mr.%20Kim%2C%20Kakao's%20founder%2C,basis%20for%20his%20internet%20empire.\">was arrested Tuesday</a> in Seoul, South Korea. That might not mean much to Westerners, but the story is a bizarre tale of how a celebrated, self-made tech billionaire fell from grace... partly because he bought a scandal-ridden K-pop agency.</p>\n<p id=\"gw7Okk\">Kim, who also goes by Brian, stands accused of manipulating SM Entertainment\u2019s", "id": 916624, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204411/kakaotalk-kim-beom-su-kpop", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "How K-pop might lead to the downfall of Korea\u2019s richest self-made tech mogul", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T19:31:21+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Slightly pixelated \u201cKamala HQ\u201d black text over a plain lime green background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/z7PuEstLQVWBHzTNCVacNyxFnbI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73477804/KAMALA_BRAT.5.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Kamala HQ</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"e3r4wJ\">On Sunday, President Joe Biden shocked the country with his announcement that he would not seek reelection in November. He threw his support behind Vice President Kamala Harris. If elected, Harris would be the first Black and Asian American woman to become president, and her historic run <a href=\"https://x.com/WinWithBLKWomen/status/1815300802359026153\">is already creating excitement</a>. Most Democrats are quickly falling in line. <a href=\"https://x.com/guiltyasinights/status/1815128122993369438\">Some</a> <a href=\"https://x.com/MichaelDrummey/status/1815184101013700883\">would say</a> <a href=\"https://x.com/RepWilson/status/181541470500495795", "id": 916625, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24203547/kamala-harris-presidential-campaign-charli-xcx-brat-summer-meme", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Kamala Harris wants you to know she\u2019s having a \u2018Brat\u2019 summer", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T18:22:36+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Spotify\u2019s CEO &amp;amp; Co-Founder Daniel Ek Joins Author &amp;amp; Comedian Trevor Noah To Discuss The Future Of Storytelling At Spotify Beach\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/jTmKG_pdgn-nTMlzHVSu2Mz-X00=/0x0:7243x4829/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73477632/1500013882.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by David M. Benett / Dave Benett / Getty Images for Spotify</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"9i4DZ0\">The saga of Spotify HiFi has many twists and turns. First announced <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24080999/spotify-hifi-lossless-high-res-audio-three-years-rip\">over three years ago</a>, the music service\u2019s higher-quality streaming tier has yet to materialize. <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/11/24175980/spotify-hifi-add-on-cost-extra-lossless-audio-supremium\">Recent reports</a> have said lossless audio will be bundled with other perks (like advanced library management, AI-powered playlists, and headphone sound quality", "id": 916626, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204520/spotify-ceo-hifi-audio-deluxe-plan-confirmed", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Spotify CEO confirms a \u2018deluxe\u2019 version with hi-fi audio is coming soon", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T17:36:25+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Wooting\u2019s 60HE keyboard\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/u99X7pdjtPsvT77FJ_vH26vTPBM=/0x0:1320x880/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73477531/wooting60he.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Wooting</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"UJuhS9\">Earlier this month, Razer <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/9/24194977/razer-snap-tap-mode-huntsman-v3-pro-wooting-rappy-snappy\">beat Wooting to a speedy new keyboard feature</a> that lets players counter-strafe more quickly in a variety of competitive PC games. Now, Wooting has implemented the same feature.</p>\n<p id=\"H80z8e\">Normally, to switch strafe directions in a first-person shooter, you have to fully release one key before pressing the other. If both are pressed, they cancel each other, and you stand there like a dummy for a moment until you release one of the keys.<strong> </strong>Professional players have mastered not overlapping A and D keys to get perfect counter-strafing and mo", "id": 916076, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204422/wooting-razer-snap-tap-socd-beta-feature", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Wooting joins Razer with a speedy new keyboard feature for PC gaming", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T16:34:43+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qZpQHCUndcR7xCG6Q0TXtsix2Do=/0x0:3000x2000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73477405/2161388655.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Alex Wong/Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"yBJj7Z\">Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer (D-NY) plans to announce in a speech that he will bring the Kids Online Safety Act (KOSA) and the Children\u2019s and Teens Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA 2.0) to the Senate floor this week for a procedural vote. This tees up the biggest step yet on the federal level to move forward with a law in the area of kids' online safety legislation.</p>\n<p id=\"o15AgC\">\u201cOver the past few months I\u2019ve met with families from across the country who have gone through the worst thing a parent could endure \u2013 losing a child,\u201d Schumer said in a statement. \u201cRather than retreating into the darkness of their loss, these families lit a candle for others ", "id": 915683, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204318/schumer-kosa-coppa-senate-floor", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Schumer plans to bring two major kids online safety bills to the Senate floor this week", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T16:24:29+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo showing an iPhone 15 laying flat on a table\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/wyVPNEecEuYBmY7YERGA969a6HY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73477364/236791_Apple_iPhone_15_and_15_Plus_review_DSeifert_0008.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Dan Seifert / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"QU3h0r\">Apple continues to work on a foldable iPhone, which could arrive as early as 2026, according to <a href=\"https://www.theinformation.com/articles/apple-moves-forward-with-foldable-iphone\">a report from <em>The Information</em></a>. The phone is rumored to fold horizontally, like the clamshell-style <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23820202/samsung-galaxy-z-flip-5-review-screen-battery-camera-hinge\">Samsung Galaxy Z Flip</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"5zQ78n\">In February, <em>The Information</em> reported that Apple was in the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/7/24064617/apple-foldable-iphone-ipad-rumor-z-flip-5\">earl", "id": 915684, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204421/apple-first-foldable-iphone-arrive-2026", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Apple\u2019s first foldable iPhone could arrive in 2026", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T16:18:11+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Netflix logo illustration\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/vSVXWKonES8d8GXk22l6-aP5I1Y=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73477354/STK072_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_2_netflix.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"VP1HNY\">There\u2019s a new name in charge of Netflix\u2019s ongoing gaming efforts. <a href=\"https://variety.com/2024/gaming/news/netflix-games-president-alain-tascan-epic-1236081464/\">As <em>Variety</em> reports</a>, the streamer has hired Alain Tascan as the new president of its gaming division, after he previously served as executive VP of game development at <em>Fortnite</em> maker Epic Games. The news comes as the game division\u2019s former boss, Mike Verdu, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/12/24177141/netflixs-gaming-boss-is-moving-to-another-role-at-netflix-in-gaming\">moved into a different role at Netflix</a> focused on a new team \u201con the cutting edge ", "id": 915685, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204447/netflix-president-of-games-alain-tascan", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Netflix has a new gaming boss after hiring former Epic exec", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T16:04:37+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Call of Duty illustration\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/dSZYplNhhy57eDLzPLOPvQIor84=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73477334/modern_warfare_3_graphic_price.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Activision</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"YzlLyA\">Microsoft is bringing last year\u2019s <em>Call of Duty: Modern Warfare III </em>to Xbox Game Pass <a href=\"https://news.xbox.com/en-us/2024/07/23/modern-warfare-3-coming-to-game-pass-july-24/\">tomorrow</a>. It\u2019s the first time a <em>Call of Duty</em> game will be available on Game Pass, and it\u2019s the last in Activision\u2019s franchise to have PlayStation-exclusive content now that Microsoft owns Activision Blizzard.</p>\n<p id=\"OfrA98\"><em>Call of Duty: Modern Warfare III </em>will be available for Xbox Game Pass for Console, PC Game Pass, and Xbox Game Pass Ultimate on July 24th. The announcement comes just weeks after Microsoft revealed <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/9/", "id": 915686, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24195537/call-of-duty-xbox-game-pass-modern-warfare-3", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Microsoft is bringing Call of Duty: Modern Warfare III to Xbox Game Pass", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T15:40:18+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Major IT outage hits banks, airlines, and businesses worldwide\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NwrOqEaI9uLU7jcxCgQwxpZNpso=/0x0:8256x5504/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73476928/2162005028.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Harun Ozalp / Anadolu via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"yEg2DQ\">On Friday morning, shortly after midnight in New York, disaster started to unfold around the world. In Australia, shoppers were met with Blue Screen of Death (BSOD) messages at self-checkout aisles. In the UK, Sky News had to suspend its broadcast after servers and PCs started crashing. In Hong Kong and India, airport check-in desks began to fail. By the time morning rolled around in New York, millions of Windows computers had crashed, and a global tech disaster was underway.</p>\n<p id=\"88prlk\">In the early hours of the outage, there was confusion over what was going on. How were so many Windows machines suddenly showing a blue", "id": 915138, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204196/crowdstrike-windows-bsod-faulty-update-microsoft-responses", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "The 78 minutes that took down millions of Windows machines", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T15:16:08+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Key art for Helldivers 2 featuring several divers in heroic poses under the text \u201cHelldivers 2 Escalation of Freedom\u201d\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Av_0VavRYmjn8NagztmqJbKCoiQ=/146x0:1583x958/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73476873/Screenshot_2024_07_23_at_10.54.05_AM.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Arrowhead Studios</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"O1vtsV\">The team at Arrowhead Game Studios is working on the biggest <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/gaming/24071317/helldivers-2-starship-troopers-video-game-great\"><em>Helldivers 2</em></a> update yet. On August 6th, the Escalation of Freedom update will offer players new game modes, enemies, mission objectives, and a much more punishing difficulty. In the announcement trailer, chief creative officer Johan Pilestedt and design director Niklas Malmborg went over the details, sharing that they\u2019re planning on bringing back an old enemy from the original <em>Helldivers</em> to t", "id": 915139, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204325/helldivers-2-update-release-date-playstation-arrowhead-studios", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Helldivers 2 is getting its biggest update very soon", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T15:02:39+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Illustration showing Amazon\u2019s logo on a black, orange, and tan background, formed by outlines of the letter \u201cA.\u201d\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Y6eYK2ELAuyYyA4dLPA_mXoVDxM=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73476827/acastro_STK103__04.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Alex Castro / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Mvw3xs\">Amazon\u2019s plan to launch a paid version of Alexa is part of a strategy change to reverse the over $25 billion in losses that its devices business incurred from 2017 to 2021, according to <a href=\"https://www.wsj.com/tech/amazon-alexa-devices-echo-losses-strategy-25f2581a\">a report from <em>The Wall Street Journal</em></a>. The AI-supercharged Alexa, which is rumored to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/21/24183013/amazon-alexa-ai-subscription\">cost up to $10 / month</a>, could arrive as soon as this month.</p>\n<p id=\"nNod24\">With a potential launch just weeks away, employe", "id": 915140, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204260/amazon-25-billion-losses-echo-devices-alexa-subscription", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Amazon\u2019s paid Alexa is coming to fill a $25 billion hole dug by Echo devices", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T15:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Meta logo on a blue background\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kuq-B37Rd2jkZNXdQZDUjjPWc3g=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73476794/STK043_VRG_Illo_N_Barclay_4_Meta.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Nick Barclay / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"KxP8Sq\">Back in April, Meta teased that it was working on a first for the AI industry: an open-source model with performance that matched the best private models from companies like OpenAI. </p>\n<p id=\"zZLDcw\">Today, that model has arrived. Meta is releasing Llama 3.1, the largest-ever open-source AI model, which the company claims outperforms <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/5/13/24155493/openai-gpt-4o-launching-free-for-all-chatgpt-users\">GPT-4o</a> and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/6/20/24181961/anthropic-claude-35-sonnet-model-ai-launch\">Anthropic\u2019s Claude 3.5 Sonnet</a> on several benchmarks. It\u2019s also making the Llama-based Meta AI assistan", "id": 915141, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204055/meta-ai-llama-3-1-open-source-assistant-openai-chatgpt", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Meta releases the biggest and best open-source AI model yet", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T14:53:15+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Two red and white Supras\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Opo0-dokaybZJrpswYIYZCOfv0Y=/105x0:1995x1260/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73476788/TRI_Tandem_Drift_Hero.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Toyota</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"yztGEJ\">Toyota Research Institute (TRI) and Stanford are plugging AI into two Supras that pull off Formula Drift-style tandem driving \u2014 but they\u2019re looking for something more important than style points.</p>\n<p id=\"LdifWS\"><a href=\"https://pressroom.toyota.com/toyota-research-institute-and-stanford-engineering-achieve-worlds-first-fully-autonomous-tandem-drift-sequence/\">In a press release</a>, TRI\u2019s VP of human interactive driving, Avinash Balachandran, says that drifting two cars in tandem autonomously is a \u201cmilestone\u201d and has \u201cfar-reaching implications for building advanced safety systems\u201d in future passenger vehicles.</p>\n<p id=\"MjEdzR\">Beyond the impressive showing, which <a href=\"https:/", "id": 915142, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204309/stanford-toyota-supra-ai-self-driving-autonomous-drifting", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Tandem drifting Toyotas show how AI might help drivers on slippery roads", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T14:48:32+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"President Biden stands at a podium with a wall behind him that says \u201chistoric climate action\u201d\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ooz3MSDZbWbb8H8QZ1szPiTKC-8=/0x0:5149x3433/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73476780/1793259269.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>President Joe Biden delivers remarks during a climate event at the White House complex on November 14th, 2023, in Washington, DC.</em> | Photo by Win McNamee / Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ptjyMd\">Greenhouse gas emissions are falling in the US thanks to major investments in clean energy and transportation \u2014 but it\u2019s not happening fast enough, a new report shows. As a result, the US isn\u2019t on track to meet the ambitious climate goals set by the Biden administration as the president enters his final months in office. Political upheaval and soaring electricity demand from AI, crypto, and EVs risk pushing those goals further out of reach.</p>\n<p id=\"AkW68p\">The latest ", "id": 915143, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24203766/biden-us-climate-clean-energy-forecast-rhodium", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "We\u2019re at a make-or-break moment for US climate goals", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T14:16:30+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A Cruise Origin, viewed from the side. It\u2019s a bread loaf-shaped van. glossy white and black on the side and with an orange roof.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/NxnKeSIgFHsxoR3nZkCwT-C6H-E=/232x126:1809x1177/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73476727/vpavic_200121_3874_0010.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Cruise Origin in 2020.</em> | Image: Vjeran Pavic / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"XPm1Dn\">General Motors told reporters on Tuesday that it has indefinitely suspended production of its self-driving Cruise Origin robotaxi, <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2024/07/23/business/general-motors-cruise-driverless-taxi.html\">reports <em>The New York Times</em></a>. The company will refocus on using the Chevy Bolt EV, which Cruise has already been using. A modified version will go into production next year.</p>\n<p id=\"6kVMXt\">The Origin created \u201cregulatory uncertainty\u201d owing to its design, GM CEO Mary Barra said in her <a ", "id": 914654, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204251/gm-cruise-suspends-origin-robotaxi-production-chevy-bolt-ev-self-driving", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "GM ditches Cruise\u2019s custom-designed driverless car", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T14:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The AM RGB 65 keyboard on a desk mat alongside a mouse, mug, Analogue Pocket, and Game Boy Color. The keyboard is turned on and showing a variety of colorful LEDs under its keys and on its dot matrix display.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5-G6JkKDgqfPFWLHFsHXKmvvPi8=/0x0:5950x3967/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73476665/072224_Angry_Miao_AM_RGB_65_ADiBenedetto_0007.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The gray model may lack some of the Game Boy\u2019s vintage vibes like the other colors on offer, but the design homages are there once you look close.</em></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p class=\"p-large-text\" id=\"EydFD2\">Between the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22831589/analogue-pocket-review\">Analogue Pocket</a> and the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24139004/apple-app-store-retro-game-emulators-ios-console-ports-storystream\">proliferation of game emulators</a> <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24150467/delta-emulator-apple-app-voi", "id": 914655, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204005/angry-miao-am-rgb-65-nintendo-game-boy-mechanical-keyboard-price-specs", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Angry Miao\u2019s new $559 mechanical keyboard has Game Boy vibes", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T13:42:15+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image of a crashed Windows PC over a Vergecast illustration\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/W2n4M1muyNEe1w36zZp1xsPHCxI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73476600/VST_0723_Site.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo: Andrey Rudakov / Bloomberg via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"XABhQC\">It all started with a configuration file. A seemingly routine update, the kind that happens hundreds of times a year to millions of computers around the world. But last week, that update <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/20/24202527/crowdstrike-microsoft-windows-bsod-outage\">crashed 8.5 million computers</a> and wreaked havoc on banks, airlines, schools, and more.</p>\n<p id=\"NkPqSC\">On <a href=\"https://link.chtbl.com/vergecast\">this episode of <em>The Vergecast</em></a>, <em>The Verge</em>\u2019s <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/authors/tom-warren\">Tom Warren</a> joins the show to talk about the story and legacy of <a ", "id": 914656, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204077/crowdstrike-windows-crash-exercise-apps-vergecast", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Inside the global computer crash", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T13:30:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of two hands emerging from phones, one holding a credit card and one holding cash.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/73iDBXaxYLEPptXouSynalwE3d8=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73476574/STK417_Mobile_Banking_1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Hugo Herrera / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"51p5Yy\">Nearly a decade ago, Uber revealed that customers are <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2016/5/20/11721890/uber-surge-pricing-low-battery\">more willing to pay surge prices</a> when their phones are about to die. That data point sparked a pervasive belief that Uber and other ridehailing apps use algorithms to tailor each passenger\u2019s price to their behavior and willingness to pay \u2014 a practice known as \u201csurveillance pricing.\u201d A related myth \u2014 that <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fthriftytraveler.com%2Fguides%2Fsearching-incognito-for-flights%2F&a", "id": 914270, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204011/ftc-surveillance-pricing-investigation-mckinsey-mastercard-chase", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Are you being exploited by AI-powered surveillance pricing?", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T13:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An example of Adobe Illustrator\u2019s new Generative Shape Fill&amp;nbsp;feature.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ye0mCYXJaPGTefCYhtVuOv5_14Q=/0x0:1620x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73476493/Gen_Shape_Fill_4.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Illustrator\u2019s new Generative Shape Fill tool allows users to fill a selected shape with scalable generated images.</em> | Image: Adobe</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"OxKvl7\">Adobe is introducing some new tools and generative AI features to its Illustrator and Photoshop design software that aim to help speed up creative workflows. The most notable updates are coming to Illustrator courtesy of Adobe\u2019s new Firefly Vector 2 AI model, which is available in public beta starting today.</p>\n<p id=\"kpu6GD\">Firefly Vector 2 powers new Illustrator features like Generative Shape Fill, which allows users to add detailed vectors to shapes via descriptive text prompts. The updated model also improves th", "id": 914271, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24204231/adobe-photoshop-illustrator-generative-ai-firefly-vector-features", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Adobe rolls out more generative AI features to Illustrator and Photoshop", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T12:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing Prime Video\u2019s new UI on a TV\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/7w9lo9zSILDCFplQMCYabjYrpZo=/160x0:1888x1152/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73476378/amazon_prime_video_ui_update_1.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Amazon</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"ZPQPHP\">Amazon\u2019s Prime Video is fixing one of the most frustrating things about its interface. <a href=\"https://www.aboutamazon.com/news/entertainment/prime-video-updated-steaming-experience\">Its redesigned UI comes with</a> a new tab dedicated to all the content included with your Prime Video subscription \u2014 no paid movies or series mixed in.</p>\n<p id=\"RS7eEU\">You\u2019ll find the new \u201cPrime\u201d tab in the main navigation bar that\u2019s now situated at the top of the screen, rather than on the left side. Alongside options for movies, TV shows, sports, and live TV, there are tabs dedicated to other services you\u2019re subscribed to, such as Max, Crunchyroll, and Paramount Plus. I", "id": 913856, "language": "en-US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/7/23/24203748/amazon-prime-video-interface-update", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 86, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "source_obj__id": 359, "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Amazon\u2019s Prime Video is making it easier to find what\u2019s free to watch", "user": null, "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-07-23T11:00:00+00:00", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A black robot vacuum on a hardwood floor with a mop extended above it and a big, black charging dock behind it.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/neCTBRjR4t-BumDQlxIOigZjZ9M=/0x202:1572x1250/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73476320/RoombaCombo_10Max_AutoWash_Photo_Lifestyle_ArmLifting_WetTrail.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Roomba Combo 10 Max is the company\u2019s first robot vacuum with a charging dock that can wash the bot\u2019s mop as well as empty its bin and refill its mopping tank.</em> | Imge: iRobot</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"xV0YSP\">The <a href=\"https://www.anrdoezrs.net/links/8532386/type/dlg/sid/verge/https://www.irobot.com/en_US/roomba-combo-10-max-robot-with-autowash-dock/X085020.html\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Roomba Combo 10 Max</a> is a new robot vacuum and mop from iRobot that can wash its mop, empty its bin, and refill its mopping tank \u2014 meaning less manual labor on your part. The compa", "id": 913465, "lang